address: Xã Tuấn Việt, Huyện Kim Thành, Tỉnh Hải Dương
thought:
**Navigating the Reorganization of "Xã Tuấn Việt"**

Okay, so I've been asked to figure out the new administrative unit(s) for the old address "Xã Tuấn Việt, Huyện Kim Thành, Tỉnh Hải Dương". This is a classic case of navigating administrative boundary changes. My thought process here is to be methodical and thorough.

First, I identified "Tỉnh Hải Dương" (Hải Dương Province) as the old province. Immediately, my experience tells me to check for provincial mergers. Looking at relevant resolutions (like 60-NQ/TW), I confirmed that "Tỉnh Hải Dương" was indeed merged into "Thành phố Hải Phòng" (Hải Phòng City). So, we're now dealing with Hải Phòng.

Next, I focused on "Xã Tuấn Việt" (Tuấn Việt Commune) itself. I started searching for resolutions related to Hải Phòng and, of course, the now-obsolete Hải Dương. Resolution "1669/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của thành phố Hải Phòng" proved crucial. This is where the real work begins.

Line 70 of the resolution specifically mentions "Xã Tuấn Việt" being partly merged into a new commune called "Xã Nam An Phụ". Then, Line 110 states that the *remaining* part of "Xã Tuấn Việt" (after the Nam An Phụ merge) is folded into the new commune "Xã Lai Khê". Brilliant!

To confirm, I needed to locate these two new communes in the system. I checked the "New wards" list, and sure enough, found: "Xã Nam An Phụ" (with its specific code and the province, Hải Phòng) and "Xã Lai Khê" (same information).

Confidence in this finding is very high. The resolution is explicit about "Xã Tuấn Việt" being split and incorporated into these two new entities. There's no room for doubt here.

Thus, my JSON output will contain both "Xã Nam An Phụ" and "Xã Lai Khê" as the possible new administrative units, as a part of the address "Xã Tuấn Việt, Huyện Kim Thành, Tỉnh Hải Dương." This is now a simple matter of preparing the output in the correct format.
